Reasoning: The paper focuses on the maintenance and evolution of FLOSS projects, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The survey methodology used to gather data from core developers also involves aspects of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses project characteristics and barriers faced by core developers, which could be relevant to the software development (cs.SD) and computing and communication (cs.CC) sub-categories.
